01:09:09.600 --> 01:09:14.600
But if a day, two, three weeks ago I saw a real return,

01:09:14.600 --> 01:09:17.600
now I am putting even more effort,

01:09:17.600 --> 01:09:20.600
and the result is the same.

01:09:20.600 --> 01:09:24.600
I am slowly starting to lower my hands again.

01:09:24.600 --> 01:09:27.600
And this is the second barrier of overcoming.

01:09:27.600 --> 01:09:33.600
Look, the second part of the graph is the part of euphoria.

01:09:33.600 --> 01:09:38.600
I exceeded my expectations and I achieved a greater result.

01:09:38.600 --> 01:09:41.600
And now comes the third part,

01:09:41.600 --> 01:09:47.600
when my expectations are unjustified or too fast.

01:09:47.600 --> 01:09:49.600
They have increased,

01:09:49.600 --> 01:09:56.600
and my achievements do not meet my expectations.

01:09:56.600 --> 01:10:01.600
And then my motivation and my activity fall again.

01:10:01.600 --> 01:10:08.600
And this is the situation that occurs very often after training,

01:10:08.600 --> 01:10:11.600
after training of the staff.

01:10:11.600 --> 01:10:14.600
It seems that people are successful,

01:10:14.600 --> 01:10:16.600
they have completed training,

01:10:16.600 --> 01:10:18.600
they have gained new knowledge.

01:10:18.600 --> 01:10:21.600
They would only now be able to better implement sales plans.

01:10:21.600 --> 01:10:24.600
And after a successful training,

01:10:24.600 --> 01:10:27.600
the indicators fall.

01:10:27.600 --> 01:10:29.600
And, accordingly, the question arises,

01:10:29.600 --> 01:10:33.600
why did I spend money on training?

01:10:33.600 --> 01:10:36.600
I am a manager.

01:10:36.600 --> 01:10:44.600
This is the barrier that is often associated with the fact

01:10:44.600 --> 01:10:50.600
that the training results that I expected do not meet.

01:10:50.600 --> 01:10:52.600
My competence falls.

01:10:52.600 --> 01:10:56.600
It naturally remains much higher than the initial level of competence.

01:10:56.600 --> 01:11:00.600
But now I am approaching the second barrier of overcoming.

01:11:00.600 --> 01:11:04.600
And now I am starting to look for new alternative options.

01:11:04.600 --> 01:11:08.600
I am starting to look for new ways

01:11:08.600 --> 01:11:12.600
not to increase my competence,

01:11:12.600 --> 01:11:18.600
but at least to keep it at the level that I have already reached.

01:11:18.600 --> 01:11:22.600
Look, because of the discrepancy in the expectation of competence,

01:11:22.600 --> 01:11:27.600
my competence fell a little lower.

01:11:27.600 --> 01:11:31.600
The barrier of overcoming is higher than the initial level of competence,

01:11:31.600 --> 01:11:33.600
but lower than what I had.

01:11:33.600 --> 01:11:35.600
I want to cling to this level.

01:11:35.600 --> 01:11:37.600
I am starting to be afraid.

01:11:37.600 --> 01:11:40.600
What if I will fall down to my original competence?

01:11:40.600 --> 01:11:44.600
What if I am so useless and incapable?

01:11:44.600 --> 01:11:47.600
And then I have two options again.

01:11:47.600 --> 01:11:50.600
Either I put my hands down here

01:11:50.600 --> 01:11:54.600
and try to find alternative ways of behaviour,

01:11:54.600 --> 01:11:56.600
a new job,

01:11:56.600 --> 01:12:00.600
stop taking the initiative,

01:12:00.600 --> 01:12:06.600
find new ways that will allow me to keep my competence,

01:12:06.600 --> 01:12:08.600
even if it has fallen a little,

01:12:08.600 --> 01:12:13.600
or I am able to overcome this barrier.

01:12:13.600 --> 01:12:17.600
Again, just to understand with the help of other people's support,

01:12:17.600 --> 01:12:20.600
with the help of competent leadership,

01:12:20.600 --> 01:12:22.600
that in fact it is normal.

01:12:22.600 --> 01:12:25.600
I have overestimated my expectations about my first results.

01:12:25.600 --> 01:12:27.600
But it's all good.

01:12:27.600 --> 01:12:29.600
I will achieve what I want.

01:12:29.600 --> 01:12:31.600
I will achieve my level of competence.

01:12:31.600 --> 01:12:34.600
But I just need to put more effort and spend more time.

01:12:34.600 --> 01:12:39.600
If a person understands this and receives support,

01:12:39.600 --> 01:12:42.600
then the fourth stage is coming.

01:12:42.600 --> 01:12:48.600
I will not look for alternative ways to maintain my slippery competence.

01:12:48.600 --> 01:12:55.600
I will put more effort to maintain my competence

01:12:55.600 --> 01:12:59.600
and it will reach the desired level quickly.

01:12:59.600 --> 01:13:01.600
This is what the fourth stage ends with.

01:13:01.600 --> 01:13:08.600
When my level of competence is still higher than the one I had before.

01:13:08.600 --> 01:13:10.600
Compare these two points.

01:13:11.600 --> 01:13:19.600
This is the stage when I automatically use a new skill.

01:13:19.600 --> 01:13:26.600
When the motivation I have reaches the desired level.

01:13:26.600 --> 01:13:30.600
This is the stage when you can't stop.

01:13:30.600 --> 01:13:34.600
So, the fifth stage is coming.

01:13:34.600 --> 01:13:36.600
Here is the number 5 that you see on the graph.

01:13:36.600 --> 01:13:43.600
This stage is characterized by the fact that you have reached the level of expected competence.

01:13:43.600 --> 01:13:46.600
And this competence has become automatic for you.

01:13:46.600 --> 01:13:51.600
As automatic as it was for you at the initial level.

01:13:51.600 --> 01:13:58.600
Only now you automatically have the skill of performing certain or other professional actions.

01:13:58.600 --> 01:14:01.600
Motivation formation is at a completely new level.

01:14:01.600 --> 01:14:05.600
You have reached your level of competence.

01:14:05.600 --> 01:14:07.600
Moreover, you have even surpassed it.

01:14:07.600 --> 01:14:16.600
Now, just like before, you can transfer the successful actions you have,

01:14:16.600 --> 01:14:21.600
the skill you have acquired, to a new sphere of activity.

01:14:21.600 --> 01:14:25.600
And it often turns out that in new spheres of activity,

01:14:25.600 --> 01:14:30.600
the skill you have developed leads to new achievements.

01:14:31.600 --> 01:14:35.600
In the sense that it turns out to be useful there as well.

01:14:35.600 --> 01:14:39.600
You have developed the skill of management so well,

01:14:39.600 --> 01:14:46.600
that you can now manage not only two or three managers who work with you,

01:14:46.600 --> 01:14:51.600
but you can also manage a department, your own company.

01:14:51.600 --> 01:14:52.600
You can start your own business.

01:14:52.600 --> 01:14:54.600
You have acquired the skill of time management.

01:14:54.600 --> 01:14:56.600
You have acquired the skill of management.

01:14:57.600 --> 01:14:59.600
And now you transfer this skill to a new sphere.

01:14:59.600 --> 01:15:05.600
This is where the point of leap-forward development comes in.

01:15:05.600 --> 01:15:09.600
It is called the starting point of the synergetic effect.

01:15:09.600 --> 01:15:12.600
This is where the fifth stage ends.

01:15:12.600 --> 01:15:18.600
When you are able to apply a successful model of activity,

01:15:18.600 --> 01:15:21.600
a successful model of motivation, to a new sphere.

01:15:21.600 --> 01:15:24.600
You set yourself new goals.

01:15:24.600 --> 01:15:28.600
And now, without thinking about it,

01:15:28.600 --> 01:15:36.600
you reach the most successful expectation

01:15:36.600 --> 01:15:41.600
that you had at the end of the first stage.

01:15:41.600 --> 01:15:45.600
This is where the point of knowledge transfer to a professional context is.

01:15:45.600 --> 01:15:48.600
You have raised your expectations there.

01:15:48.600 --> 01:15:52.600
And here the second point of regression with the barrier of overcoming arose.

01:15:53.600 --> 01:15:57.600
Now you automatically, without your special thinking,

01:15:57.600 --> 01:15:59.600
without your special efforts,

01:15:59.600 --> 01:16:02.600
you have reached this level of competence.

01:16:02.600 --> 01:16:08.600
This is how a person's motivation is formed.

01:16:08.600 --> 01:16:12.600
But when you reach a new level of competence,

01:16:12.600 --> 01:16:15.600
the sixth stage, which you see,

01:16:15.600 --> 01:16:18.600
everything starts from the beginning.

01:16:18.600 --> 01:16:22.600
Only now, with your initial competence,

01:16:22.600 --> 01:16:24.600
with your initial level of development,

01:16:24.600 --> 01:16:26.600
you will reach the expectation.

01:16:26.600 --> 01:16:29.600
But then you set yourself new goals.

01:16:29.600 --> 01:16:34.600
And so, in a circle, we set ourselves new and new goals,

01:16:34.600 --> 01:16:38.600
new and new tasks, and we achieve them.

01:16:38.600 --> 01:16:42.600
We can stop at the level reached,

01:16:42.600 --> 01:16:45.600
but then it will be our choice.

01:16:45.600 --> 01:16:51.600
This will mean that we are satisfied with the level of achievement we have reached.

01:16:51.600 --> 01:16:56.600
Or we are afraid to lose what has already been achieved.

01:16:56.600 --> 01:16:59.600
Therefore, it is better, as they say, not to twitch.

01:16:59.600 --> 01:17:02.600
If a person stops here,

01:17:02.600 --> 01:17:05.600
he remains a successful leader,

01:17:05.600 --> 01:17:10.600
who first rests on the achievements,

01:17:10.600 --> 01:17:14.600
and then either gives way to another,

01:17:14.600 --> 01:17:17.600
or he has to develop further.

01:17:17.600 --> 01:17:21.600
If a person does not stop at this level of motivation,

01:17:21.600 --> 01:17:23.600
he sets himself new expectations,

01:17:23.600 --> 01:17:26.600
and again implements the same schedule,

01:17:26.600 --> 01:17:28.600
with all the same points of regression,

01:17:28.600 --> 01:17:31.600
with all the same barriers of overcoming once again.

01:17:31.600 --> 01:17:37.600
But now this schedule will be implemented faster and easier.

01:17:37.600 --> 01:17:43.600
Just because you already have your own experience of overcoming points of regression,

01:17:43.600 --> 01:17:46.600
you already know the mechanism,

01:17:46.600 --> 01:17:49.600
you already know that you are able to do it.

01:17:49.600 --> 01:17:52.600
And the schedule is compressed over time.

01:17:52.600 --> 01:17:57.600
You need less and less time to move from the first stage to the sixth,

01:17:57.600 --> 01:18:01.600
to move from the initial level of competition to a higher one,

01:18:01.600 --> 01:18:03.600
the one you set for yourself.

01:18:03.600 --> 01:18:07.600
This is a very important curve,

